'''Radiologists without Borders''' is a 401(c)(3) [[non-profit organization]] that delivers humanitarian aid to developing countries, in the form of radiological services and equipment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.itnonline.com/content/radiologists-without-borders-heart-radiology |title=Radiologists Without Borders: The Heart of Radiology &#124; ITN Online |format= |work= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.latribuna.hn/2012/03/09/radiologos-sin-fronteras-donan-equipo-medico/ |title=Radiólogos sin Fronteras donan equipo médico - LaTribuna.hn |format= |work= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref name=tanz1>{{cite web |url=http://www.healthimaginghub.com/medical-imaging/2879-tanzanian-radiologists-receive-mammography-and-breast-cancer-training-at-lourdes-hospital.html |title=Tanzanian Radiologists Receive Mammography and Breast Cancer Training at Lourdes Hospital |work= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref name=web>{{cite web |url=http://www.rwborders.org |title=Radiologists without Borders &#124; Saving lives, one image at a time |format= |work= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref name=tanz3>{{cite web |url=http://www.lourdes.com/about-us/media-center/releases/2011/3/tanzanian-clinicians |title=Lourdes Hospital - Lourdes Hospital Hosts Tanzanian Clinicians For Advanced Training in Mammography - Binghamton, NY |format= |work= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref name=tanz2>{{cite web |url=http://usa.humanityfirst.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=198 |title=Humanity First USA Responds to Drought Crisis in Tanzania, East Africa |format= |work= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref name=tanz4>{{cite web |url=http://174.132.155.186/business/14-international-business/8986-tanzanians-receive-mammography-training-at-top-american-hospital.html |title=Tanzanians receive mammography training at top American hospital |work= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.acr.org/Membership/Volunteering/International-Outreach/Useful-Links |title=Useful Links - American College of Radiology |format= |work= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elheraldo.hn/Secciones-Principales/Pais/Brigadas-medicas-dejan-Honduras-por-inseguridad |title=Brigadas médicas dejan Honduras por inseguridad - Diario El Heraldo de Honduras |format= |work= |accessdate=}}</ref> Radiologists without Borders was founded in 2008, by New York-based radiologist Tariq Gill.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rad-aid.org/project.aspx?pageName=2012%20RAD-AID%20Conference |title=2012 RAD-AID Conference on International Radiology for Developing Countries |format= |work= |accessdate=}}</ref> The organization is composed entirely of volunteers, and its mission statement is "to bring life saving diagnostic imaging solutions to medically underserved populations worldwide."<ref name=web />

Radiologists without Borders began work in Haiti after the [[2010 Haiti earthquake|2010 earthquake]]. They have provided an ultrasound to the City Hospital and provided training of medical personnel.<ref name=web /> The group worked with [[Muhimbili University of Health and Allied Sciences|Muhimbili University of Health and Allied Sciences (MUHAS)]] and Muhimbili Hospital in 2010 and 2011 to research needs of the school and university. Radiologists without Borders arranged for training of medical personnel which took place at [[Lourdes Hospital (New York)|Lourdes Hospital]] in Binghamton, New York, has donated 2 mammography machines, and textbooks and computers for the school.<ref name=tanz1 /><ref name=web /><ref name=tanz3 /><ref name=tanz2 /><ref name=tanz4 />

